  "why": "The paper provides substantive diagnostic insight tying observed failures and coverage responses to model internals and statistical failure patterns (e.g., neuron output distributions, out-of-range activations, covariance/variance, and sensitivity to sample quantity vs. diversity). It empirically isolates causes (for example, showing that some prior coverage metrics respond to ‘‘dissimilarity’’ or out-of-range neuron outputs introduced by adversarial perturbations rather than to true fault-revealing capability) and also links certain failure classes to a known vulnerability (texture-bias) via controlled transformations. However, the analysis remains at the level of model internals and statistical patterns rather than giving deep, per-failure root-cause analyses for all discovered errors (e.g., comprehensive linking of every discovered failure to specific spurious features, dataset bias, or overfitting). This matches the metric’s description of a partial diagnostic treatment.",
